# React + Vite

This template provides a minimal setup to get React working in Vite with HMR and some ESLint rules.

Currently, two official plugins are available:

- [@vitejs/plugin-react](https://github.com/vitejs/vite-plugin-react/blob/main/packages/plugin-react/README.md) uses [Babel](https://babeljs.io/) for Fast Refresh
- [@vitejs/plugin-react-swc](https://github.com/vitejs/vite-plugin-react-swc) uses [SWC](https://swc.rs/) for Fast Refresh

# alx-fe-reactjs

## Tasks

### 0. Create your first React App

**Mandatory**

1. **Create an empty repository called `alx-fe-reactjs`**

2. **Clone the repository and cd into that directory.**
    ```bash
    git clone <your-github-repo-url>
    cd alx-fe-reactjs
    ```

3. **Run the command to create your React app:**
    ```bash
    npm create vite@latest alx-react-app -- --template react
    ```

    - Here, `alx-react-app` is the name of your react app.

4. **Navigate into the newly created directory and install dependencies:**
    ```bash
    cd alx-react-app
    npm install
    ```

5. **Run the development server:**
    ```bash
    npm run dev
    ```

    - Your app should now open in your browser on port `5173`. If it doesn't open automatically, manually enter the address in your browser:
    ```
    localhost:5173
    ```

